Career summary
2018-present Director, OA MediaKraft
Responsibilities: Founded and built the company from the ground up. I have since
attracted the business to both corporate organisation to and private customers. I
conceptualised and developed her identities as well as the brand. The company is
registered in both England, United Kingdom, and Nigeria.
July 2016 - 2019 Newsletter Content Creator/Graphics Design Consultant (contract),
Academic Staff Cooperative, Lagos State University, Ojo.
Responsibilities: Led the team to establish the first newsletter. Guided the process for
public relations material and content developments on ASCOOP activities. The output
was published and circulated in digital and prints formats. All technical duties,
including layout and design, content editing, digital generation, and hardcopy printing,
were crucial components of this function.
2012- 2015 Book Layout planning/Graphic Editor, Griot Publishers
Responsibilities: Designed original journal layout and see to all print production activities.
Worked on designing covers and inside designs
2012- 2013 Page Planner/Graphic Editor, Ehingbeti Media, Publisher of Eko Akete News
Responsibilities: Conceptualised and designed the weekly community newspaper layout
and prepare the artwork for press production.
2013- 2021 Graphic Editor/Consultant, LASUGONG Newspaper & LASU Quill
Responsibilities: Designed entire issues (32+) using Adobe InDesign, CorelDraw, and
Photoshop. Led the 2018 team to surpass record by creating a new brand for both
LASUGONG and Quill publications. The brands attracted thousands more sales and the
publication were relaunched as the University flagbearer publication. On the same feat,
the brand attracted external funding support for expansion.
